### Locale Tiers
```javascript
const LOCALE_TIERS = {
  T1: ['', 'de', 'uk', 'fr', 'jp'],
  T2: ['dk', 'es', 'fi', 'it', 'nl', 'no', 'se'],
  T3: ['ca', 'mx', 'la', 'kr', 'br', 'hk_zh', 'tw', 'cn'],
  T4: [
    'eg_ar', 'kw_ar', 'mena_ar', 'qa_ar', 'sa_ar', 'bg', 'cz', 'at', 'ch_de', 'lu_de',
    'gr_el', 'in', 'id_en', 'my_en', 'ph_en', 'th_en', 'za', 'africa', 'gr_en', 'hk_en',
    'ng', 'vn_en', 'au', 'nz', 'be_en', 'cis_en', 'eg_en', 'ie', 'il_en', 'kw_en', 'lu_en',
    'mena_en', 'qa_en', 'sa_en', 'sg', 'ae_en', 'co', 'pe', 'cl', 'cr', 'ec', 'gt', 'ar', 'pr', 'ee',
    'ph_fil', 'ca_fr', 'ch_fr', 'be_fr', 'lu_fr', 'il_he', 'in_hi', 'hu', 'id_id', 'ch_it',
    'lv', 'my_ms', 'be_nl', 'pl', 'pt', 'ro', 'cis_ru', 'sk', 'si', 'th_th', 'tr', 'ua', 'vn_vi'
  ]
};

// Get all locales for a specific tier or multiple tiers
function getLocalesByTier(tiers = ['T1']) {
  return tiers.flatMap(tier => LOCALE_TIERS[tier] || []);
}

// Example: getLocalesByTier(['T1', 'T2']) => ['', 'de', 'uk', 'fr', 'jp', 'dk', 'es', ...]
```

### Building URLs
```javascript
function buildPlansUrl(locale, page = 'plans') {
  const baseUrl = 'https://www.adobe.com';
  const localePrefix = locale ? `/${locale}` : '';
  return `${baseUrl}${localePrefix}/creativecloud/${page}.html`;
}

// Example: buildPlansUrl('fr') => 'https://www.adobe.com/fr/creativecloud/plans.html'
// Example: buildPlansUrl('') => 'https://www.adobe.com/creativecloud/plans.html'
```

### Test Configuration
When writing tests or monitors for multiple locales:
- **Prioritize by tier:** Test T1 first, then T2, T3, and finally T4
- Group by region for parallel execution
- Consider timezone differences for scheduling
- Account for different pricing/currency displays
- Test both left-to-right (LTR) and right-to-left (RTL) languages (Arabic locales)
- For smoke tests, focus on T1 locales only
- For comprehensive testing, include T1-T3; T4 can be run less frequently

## Notes
- Total: 92 supported locales (90 with prefixes + 2 special cases)
- **Locale Tiers:** T1 (5), T2 (7), T3 (8), T4 (69)
- RTL languages: Arabic variants (eg_ar, kw_ar, qa_ar, sa_ar, ae_ar, mena_ar) and Hebrew (il_he)
- Multi-language countries: Belgium (3), Luxembourg (3), Switzerland (3), Egypt (2), Greece (2), etc.
- Empty string ('') represents US locale (no prefix in URL)
- Priority testing should focus on T1 first, then T2, T3, and finally T4

